      <item>
        <title>Suspending Readrz Services</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;I am suspending all services behind the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.readrz.com&quot;&gt;Readrz.com&lt;/a&gt; infrastructure today:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Feeds scanning service&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Duplicate finder service&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Search indexer service&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Image scanner service&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Summarizer service&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Mongo database&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Web site&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All the code (apart from AWS connection details) is released here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/akuz/readrz-public&quot;&gt;&lt;i class=&quot;fa fa-github&quot;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; akuz/readrz-public&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is a high chance that I can bring the infrastructure up again, if there is interest.
Hopefully, one day I can also release the exciting innovative JavaScript menus as standalone components.
I am keeping the database of all the news scanned between Jan, 2011 - Mar, 2015.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For now, I’ve decided to redirect $150 it costs to run it monthly to another project.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

